\f0\fs28 \cf2 Land of the Lost p3: \'93n the same way that a book is composed of many pages, a digital object may be composed of many smaller parts. For example, a web site can be thought of as a single digital object, but each of the individual HTML files and image files can also be thought of as individual digital objects. Not only must the dependencies for each individual part be accounted for, but the relationships between each component part must also be maintained, in order to preserve the context of the original.\'94}

