\f0\fs28 \cf2 Land of the lost p3: \'93On the other hand, if the library owns a digital copy of the same book, then not only will the reader have to be capable of translating from Coptic, but access will also depend on being able to open the file in a meaningful way. If the library loses access to the software used to access the file, then it might become impossible to extract any information from the object.\'94}

